Thanks to those who posted their support.  Our personal friend has died and it's been a very tough week for us.<br>
<br>
----------<br>
First, Anonposter, how about some history, so you can get your own FACTS straight:  New Tribes Missions has been actively involved in the Philippines as well as other parts of the world since well before you were born.  NTM is not a &quot;Philippine Christian Militia&quot; and had nothing to do with the 1999 incident that you related.  NTM's main focus is actually in Africa.  <br>
<br>
But before you go off saying that &quot;they knew the risks and should have stayed out...&quot; (and I'm sure this will really disapoint you) the Burnhams were taken from a holiday resort while they were on vacation along with 17 other innocent bystandards.  Vacation.  Celebrating their 18th wedding anniversary.  They weren't active involved in any &quot;fanatical&quot; activities at the time, nor where the 17 other people.  M'kay? <br>
<br>
Don't believe me?  Read this article.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/asiapcf/southeast/06/09/phil.hostages/index.html">www.cnn.com/2002/WORLD/as...index.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
Regardless, where is your patriotism, or your compassion for life?  Someone dies and you arogantly and hearlessly post that it's their own fault (when you have no idea what the real facts are).  Forget their employment, profession, or whatever, these are/were American Citizens who were held prisoner for over a year, litterally chained by the wrist 24/7/365, and eventually killed.  The others who were killed were Philippine Nationals.  From what we hear from other news reports, e-mails, etc., that country is outraged that their own people did this not only to Americans, but more so to their own people.  <br>
<br>
Oh, I see, you chose to focus on one small detail in the incident and blather on your soap box with a paper bag over your head to hide your identity.  Excellent.  Nice job there.  Congratulations on your courage to stand up and act fool.<br>
<br>
I suppose the 9-11 tragedy in NYC didn't outrage you either, huh?  Feel free to leave the country at your earliest convenience, Anonposter.<br>
--------<br>
<br>
